<task id="DitchingCopilotSDuties">
    <title>Ditching: Copilot's Duties</title>
    <shortdesc/>
    <prolog>
        <critdates>
            <!--scott.hudson-->
            <revised modified="4. Jan. 2019"/>
            <!--keith.schengili-roberts-->
            <revised modified="31. Dec. 2019"/>			
        </critdates>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm>ditching</indexterm>
                <indexterm>copilot's duties</indexterm>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>On the emergency signal switch to inter-phone and acknowledge the emergency
                    bell.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Help the pilot salvo bombs and fuselage tank.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Check to see that the gear is up.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Assist the pilot in getting wind's direction and velocity from the
                    navigator.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Release the pilot's emergency hatch.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Lower flaps as required on pilot's signal.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Notify the crew to brace for impact. </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Cut the mixture, cut switches on pilot's signal.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Brace for impact.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Abandon ship after it has stopped, check to see that the life raft has released
                    properly. If not, <b>release it manually</b>. Proceed to the rear of the ship
                    and assist the men in the rear to abandon ship. Either the pilot or the copilot
                    must take a parachute to the raft.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
